album.title: Music To Be Murdered By: Side B (Deluxe Edition)

wiki.summary: “Tone Deaf” is another self produced song on the project, this time with the frequent collaborator Luis Resto, the man behind some classic songs of Eminem like Lose Yourself. The title “Tone Deaf” is a diss to mumble rappers since they can’t jump on a beat without mumbling. The track starts by Em pretending to not hear the person on the other side of the phone, a shade at people who called him washed. The song is almost five minutes and Eminem could fill three, long verses and a hook to it. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: “Tone Deaf” is another self produced song on the project, this time with the frequent collaborator Luis Resto, the man behind some classic songs of Eminem like Lose Yourself. The title “Tone Deaf” is a diss to mumble rappers since they can’t jump on a beat without mumbling. The track starts by Em pretending to not hear the person on the other side of the phone, a shade at people who called him washed. The song is almost five minutes and Eminem could fill three, long verses and a hook to it. He talks about topics from dissing the rap game, to bragging up about his rapping skills. On March 5, 2021, Eminem released an animated lyric video as a response to Gen Z trying to cancel him. Read more on Last.fm.
